        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Set $f(x) = 2$: $\\sqrt[3]{x-1} = 2 \\implies x-1 = 8 \\implies x = 9$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Find the remainder when $x^3 - 4x^2 + 2x - 7$ is divided by $x + 1$.",
        "options": ["$-14$", "$-10$", "$-6$", "$-2$"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "By Remainder Theorem, $P(-1) = (-1)^3 - 4(1) + 2(-1) - 7 = -1 - 4 - 2 - 7 = -14$."
      },
      {
