        "explanation": "Coefficients [3, -2, 0, 1] divided by 1 yields [3, 1, 1, 2]. Quotient is $3x^2 + x + 1$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Using Descartes' Rule of Signs, how many possible positive real zeros does $P(x) = x^4 - 5x^3 + 2x^2 + 8$ have?",
