        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Multiply by $(x-3)$: $x = 3 + 4(x-3) \\implies x = 3 + 4x - 12 \\implies 3x = 9 \\implies x = 3$. But $x=3$ makes denominator zero."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Solve the inequality $\\frac{x+3}{x-1} > 2$.",
